<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.643/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-25T13:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>287. Your 653, August 24, noon.<note n="38" xml:id="d326fn38">Not
                                printed.</note> The Department’s desire is that the return of the
                            consular premises in Nanking and any ceremonies attendant thereon shall
                            take place as soon as possible without awaiting completion of repairs.
                            See Department’s 273, August 17, 6 p.m., paragraph 1, and 281, August
                            21, 8 p.m., paragraph 2, regarding temporary quarters.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>